30/05/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The 20th meeting of the EU-Romania Joint Parliamentary Committee started on Monday (29 May) at the parliament, co-chaired by the head of the Romania-EU joint committee Guido Podesta and Viorel Hrebenciuc, head of parliament's Committee on European Integration.
"Romania will be ready to accede to the EU on 1 January 2007," European Integration Minister Anca Boagiu assured participants.
Monday's session focused on progress made in response to recommendations made during the previous meeting, as well as steps must be taken with an eye to the European Commission's crucial autumn monitoring report.
The accession process is the focus of an official visit Romanian President Traian Basescu is making to France.
Talks are to cover pending reforms by the Romanian government, France's pending ratification of the Accession Treaty, and bilateral co-operation after accession.
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 30/05/06;
Rompres - 29/05/06)
